## 💡 Intuition & Thought Process

```
Step 1: UNDERSTAND
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
- ZigZag means: values must alternate UP-DOWN or DOWN-UP
- Valid:   a < b > c  OR  a > b < c
- Invalid: a < b < c  OR  a > b > c  OR  a == b

Step 2: IDENTIFY PATTERN
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
- n can be up to 10^9 → Cannot iterate step by step
- Range is small (m ≤ 75) → Matrix size is manageable
- Repeated structure → Matrix Exponentiation!

Step 3: STATE DESIGN
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
- State U(v): value v placed going UP, next must go DOWN
- State D(v): value v placed going DOWN, next must go UP
- Total states = 2m (m UP states + m DOWN states)

Step 4: APPROACH
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
- Build transition matrix T
- Use matrix exponentiation to compute T^(n-2)
- Multiply with base case dp2 (arrays of length 2)
```

