## 🔍 State Design Explained

```
For m=3 (values 1,2,3), S=6:

INDEX:   0     1     2     3     4     5
STATE:  U(1)  U(2)  U(3)  D(1)  D(2)  D(3)

U(v) = "value v was placed, came from BELOW v"
       → next value MUST be less than v

D(v) = "value v was placed, came from ABOVE v"  
       → next value MUST be greater than v

Visual Pattern:
       prev    curr    next
         1  →   3   →  1 or 2    [U(3) state: came up to 3]
         3  →   1   →  2 or 3    [D(1) state: came down to 1]
