## 🧠 Key Concepts Used

```
1. DYNAMIC PROGRAMMING
   ─────────────────────
   dp[state] = number of valid arrays ending in that state
   State transitions capture zigzag constraint

2. MATRIX EXPONENTIATION
   ──────────────────────
   When DP has fixed transitions and n is huge:
   dp[n] = T^(n-2) × dp[2]
   Compute T^k in O(log k) instead of O(k)

3. BINARY EXPONENTIATION
   ──────────────────────
   n = 13 = 1101 in binary
   T^13 = T^8 × T^4 × T^1
   Only log(n) matrix multiplications needed

4. STATE ENCODING
   ──────────────
   Encode (value, direction) as single index
   U(v) = v-1      [0 to m-1]
   D(v) = m+(v-1)  [m to 2m-1]
```

